This paper presents a framework for dynamically constructing Bayesian networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a knowledge base, which is a common topic in databases (cs.DB) and knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.AI). The paper's focus on probabilistic inference and propagation schemes suggests it may also be relevant to computational engineering (cs.CE) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
